key_insights: Trade level to level using daily, 4-hour, and 1-hour timeframes for liquidity levels
Watch futures data on 5-minute timeframe while taking entries on 1-minute for sniper entries
Chart VIX just like individual names to watch volatility structure
Don't trade against positive fundamental news - PCE inflation flat and consumer spending higher than expected is bullish
Watch where volume is decreasing as market approaches open - indicates lack of conviction
Pre-market levels are marked as interim (blue lines) vs confirmed levels (yellow) due to lighter volume
Market makers don't buy/sell SPY and QQQ options in pre-market, so watch volume flow in futures
Be patient and wait for price to come to your levels rather than chasing
Use supply and demand indicator to identify buying and selling pools
Multiple timeframe confirmation: 5-minute futures for structure, 1-minute for entry timing
Fibonacci retracements in golden zone (50-61.8%) combined with VWAP rejection is strong signal

notable_events: PCE inflation data for August released at 5:30am - same level as prior month
Government shutdown potential and massive layoffs news pending within next few days
Federal Reserve watching inflation and unemployment as two mandates
Tariffs not having negative impact on consumer spending

summary: Bill Fanter provides detailed trade recap of Friday's 100%+ winning QQQ call trade in under 2 minutes, explaining how he used positive PCE data, multi-timeframe analysis (1-min entries with 5-min futures confirmation), VIX structure, and pre-identified liquidity levels. He also took a second winning put trade using Fibonacci golden zone rejection. Emphasizes patience, waiting for price to come to levels, and not trading against positive fundamental catalysts.
